#!/bin/sh
# Module 07 — quick reference, shown by the `labhelp` command. Host-aware.
HN="$(hostname)"
cat <<EOF

  MODULE 07 — Firewalls & Filtering              (you are on: $HN)
  ------------------------------------------------------------------

  MISSION
    The firewall filters traffic between INSIDE (pc1, dns) and OUTSIDE
    (pc2, pc3, pc4). Load the ruleset, then test which pings get through and
    see the difference between DROP (silent) and REJECT (an active refusal).

  ON THE FIREWALL — manage the FORWARD ruleset:
    iptables -L FORWARD -n -v --line-numbers    show the current rules
    /rules/rules.sh                             load the teaching ruleset
    iptables -F FORWARD                          clear all rules (allow all)

  TEST FROM A WORKSTATION — ssh over, then ping across the firewall:
    ssh pc2      then:  ping -c3 pc1       (outside -> inside)
    ssh pc3      then:  ping -c3 pc1
    ssh pc4      then:  ping -c3 pc1
    exit         to come back to the firewall

    Once rules are loaded, watch HOW each ping fails:
      DROP   -> ping just times out (100% loss, no reply at all)
      REJECT -> ping says "Destination Host Unreachable" (an active refusal)

  NAME LOOKUP (DNS)     ssh pc1   then:  getent hosts coke.dreamland.com.au

  Type  netmap  for the network diagram.
  Full guide:  module-07-firewalls/LAB-GUIDE.md      Type  exit  to leave.

EOF
